# Week 1: Tutaly — Environment, Database & Infrastructure

## Goal
Get the entire development environment running: monorepo structure, Docker-based PostgreSQL + Redis, full database schema with migrations, NestJS API scaffold, Next.js 14 frontend scaffold, and a CI/CD pipeline ready for VPS deployment.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Monorepo vs. Separate Repos:** I recommend a **monorepo** structure (`tutaly/apps/api` + `tutaly/apps/web`) using npm workspaces. This keeps everything in one place, simplifies Docker Compose, and makes CI/CD easier. If you prefer separate repos, let me know.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **TypeORM vs. Prisma:** The architecture doc mentions TypeORM. I'll proceed with TypeORM, but Prisma is also a strong option with better DX and type-safety. Your call — TypeORM is fine for this project.

> [!WARNING]
> **Docker Desktop Required:** You'll need Docker Desktop installed on your Windows machine for the local PostgreSQL + Redis setup. If you don't have it, I'll provide install instructions.

